[Method]
AddColumns
[Prefix]
Odcl_ListView_
[Desc]
This method adds columns to a ListView control with the Report style set. Complete control of each column has been provided with this method, the width, justification, and optional image from the image list can or must be specified for each control. Because this method asks you to specify the insertion index, columns don't have to be added at the end, but if necessary can be added in the beginning or the middle of the existing columns. 
\par \par The column justification is to be set using:
\par 0	Left
\par 1	Center
\par 2	Right
\par \par \b Please Note:\b0 \par Because the ListView control was design exclusively for Internet Explorer, the justification for the first column will only display left justification.  We wish this design intent of Microsoft's was not so, but unfortunately this is how Mircosoft provides the control.
\par \par \b Note:\b0 \par Create list in the manor shown as follows: \par 
          (List (List x y ...) (List x y ...) ...)
\par We have found ObjectARX does not always like lists created as follows:
\par          '(x y ...) (x y ...) ... 
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
[Begin List]
[Begin List]
nColIndex
[as Integer]
sColText
[as String]
nJustification
[as Integer]
nColWidth
[as Integer]
\i[Optional] \i0 nImageListIndex
[as Integer]
[End List]
...
[End List]


[Method]
AddItem (For Report Style)
[Prefix]
Odcl_ListView_
[Desc]
This method adds a new item to the end of a ListView control and will also fill in the cells in the entire row according to how many columns have been setup. Using this method the very first cell under the first column can be specified to display an image from the image list. Use \cf1 Odcl_ListView_SetItemImage \cf0 to set the icons of any column cell.
\par \par \b Note:\b0 \par Create list in the manor shown as follows: \par 
          (List (List x y ...) (List x y ...) ...)
\par We have found ObjectARX does not always like lists created as follows:
\par          '(x y ...) (x y ...) ... 
[Arguments Return] as Integer
ProjectFileName
[Begin List]
\i[Optional] nImageIndex ...\i0
[as Integer]
sText
[as String]
\i[Optional] sColText1 sColText2 sColText3 ...\i0
[as String]
[End List]


