[Prefix]
Odcl_ListView_
[Desc]
This method inserts a new item anywhere in a ListView control and will also fill in the cells in the entire row according to how many columns have been setup. Using this method the very first cell under the first column can be specified to display an image from the image list.  Use \cf2 Odcl_ListView_SetItemImage \cf0 to set the icons of any column cell.
\par \par \b Note:\b0 \par Create list in the manor shown as follows: \par 
          (List (List x y ...) (List x y ...) ...)
\par We have found ObjectARX does not always like lists created as follows:
\par          '(x y ...) (x y ...) ... 
[Arguments Return] as Integer
ProjectFileName
nInsertRowIndex
[as Integer]
[Begin List]
nImageIndex
[as Integer]
sText
[as String]
\i[Optional] sColText1 sColText2 sColText3 ...\i0
[as String]
[End List]


